<p class="head">28<sup>th</sup> August Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span>nsented to follow me till there, to Know where I would <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> Canoe, and to take Credits, since I would not Consent <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span>ve them Any here, but asked me for Some Liquor to get <span class="AddHand-editors">[d]</span>runk on, which they reckon the most Efficatious Medicine of all, to Cure Every Disease, and andeed often proves such for it sends them to their Graves, but Example has no Effect with them their desires must be gratified, let it be Ever so Contrary to their Health<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>herefore I granted his request, but telling him at the Same time, that Drinking was Contrary to his present State of Health<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e then had Breakfast and left him to drink his Liquor, after which he was to Come after us<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span>t now blew very hard, but we Kept up to windward as much as possible, among a parcel of Islands, and we got past them, we hoisted about a yard of Sail, which was bearing us before the wind at a great rate, we saw the five Other Canoes in a Bay to the right of us, the wind being to Nigh on their left Side, they we<span class="AddHand-author">re</span> oblige to lay bye, which they well deserved, as they were Entirely out of the way, instead of Keeping to windward as we did<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I was astonished to find the fall Entirely dry, where we often Run down with half Loaded Canoes<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Coming Out, here it began to Rain very hard, which obliged us to Camp<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[51]</span></p>

